The paper discusses a self-adaptive decision-making approach for autoscaling in the cloud, which involves optimizing Quality of Service (QoS) and cost objectives for cloud-based services. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as it deals with cloud-based services and autoscaling. The paper also mentions the use of ant colony-inspired multi-objective optimization, which is a technique commonly used in Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of achieving well-compromised trade-offs, which is a topic related to Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of compromise-dominance, which is a mechanism used in Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
